2 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
3 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
4 Article – Tax – General
5 9–205.
6 (a) (1) The Comptroller may enter into reciprocal agreements on behalf of this
7 State, with the duly authorized representatives of any other state, that provide for:
8 (i) fuel tax registration of vehicles by motor carriers;
9 (ii) establishment of periodic fuel use reporting and fuel use tax
10 payment requirements by motor carriers; and
11 (iii) disbursement of money that is collected by the Comptroller and
12 is due to other states based on:
13 1. mileage travelled and fuel used in those states; and
14 2. the respective registration fees of those states.
15 (2) The Comptroller may not enter into any reciprocal agreement that
16 would affect:
17 (i) this State’s motor carrier tax rate; or
18 (ii) this State’s registration fee for motor carriers.
19 (b) In exercising the authority granted under subsection (a) of this section, the
20 Comptroller is expressly authorized to:
21 (1) enter into regional or national fuel use tax agreements;
22 (2) become a member of any regional or national conference, group,
23 compact, or similar organization of motor carrier fuel use tax administrators; and
24 (3) enforce the provisions set forth in any regional or national fuel use tax
25 agreements.
26 (c) The agreement provisions shall apply to the fuel use taxation, registration,
27 and reporting requirements of motor carriers subject to the provisions of the agreement
28 without reference to or application of any other statutes of this State.
